ackdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527768\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104gaj1665702920979.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gaj1665702920979.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gaj1665702920979.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"gaj1665702920979\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Validation in Client/Server Applications\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">In client/server applications, most of the application processing occurs in the client machines, with a central database located on a server.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gaj1665702920979__p_d45332e1_d45333e1_d45334e1\">The key features of validation in a client/server application are:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gaj1665702920979__li_d22589e1_d22590e1_d22591e1\">Validation usually occurs locally on the client.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gaj1665702920979__li_d22592e1_d22593e1_d22594e1\">Validation can involve both Uniface’s external data structure and the storage medium. For example, when validating a primary key, Uniface checks that the key is unique relative to database occurrences and also the non-database occurrences within the component’s data structure. When validation occurs locally, only the local external data structure is available for this check.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gaj1665702920979__li_d22595e1_d22596e1_d22597e1\">Performance can benefit from conducting validation on the clients, if the validation process does not involve database I/O.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gaj1665702920979__li_d22598e1_d22599e1_d22600e1\">If validation requires cross-network database I/O, validation results in a substantial network overhead. Key validation, for example, always requires database I/O.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527768\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527768\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Validation in Client/Server Applications Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Validation in Client/Server Applications In client/server applications, most of the application processing occurs in the client machines, with a central database located on a server. The key features of validation in a client/server application are: Validation usually occurs locally on the client. Validation can involve both Uniface’s external data structure and the storage medium. For example, when validating a primary key, Uniface checks that the key is unique relative to database occurrences and also the non-database occurrences within the component’s data structure. When validation occurs locally, only the local external data structure is available for this check. Performance can benefit from conducting validation on the clients, if the validation process does not involve database I/O. If validation requires cross-network database I/O, validation results in a substantial network overhead. Key validation, for example, always requires database I/O. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}